				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="1"><B>New Exclusive Velious Images *repost*</B></a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:xanthus@everlore.com">Xanthus</b></a>
				[11/30/2000-6:24:37 PM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=287570"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[14]</font></a>
				<p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><blockquote>

<B>*Bumped to the top of the news*</B><P>

<p>
We have recently received some exclusive Velious images here on Everlore from Cindy Archuleta, Verant’s Community Relations Manager. Here we have seven new images from the Iceclad Ocean to the Temple of Veeshan and more. We will be putting up even more exclusive shots before the official Velious release which is scheduled for next Tuesday.</p>
<p>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.everlore.com/ShowScreenshot.asp?image=http://209.164.24.44/exclusive/images/velious/velious1.jpg">Picture of the boat in the docks of Iceclad Ocean</a>
<li><a href="http://www.everlore.com/ShowScreenshot.asp?image=http://209.164.24.44/exclusive/images/velious/velious2.jpg">Two mobs casting spells inside a place in a dungeon</a>
<li><a href="http://www.everlore.com/ShowScreenshot.asp?image=http://209.164.24.44/exclusive/images/velious/velious3.jpg">Here is a shot of a sleeping dragon statue in the Iceclad Ocean</a>
<li><a href="http://www.everlore.com/ShowScreenshot.asp?image=http://209.164.24.44/exclusive/images/velious/velious4.jpg">An interesting scenery shot</a>
<li><a href="http://www.everlore.com/ShowScreenshot.asp?image=http://209.164.24.44/exclusive/images/velious/velious5.jpg">This image is what is believed to be inside the Temple of Veeshan</a>
<li><a href="http://www.everlore.com/ShowScreenshot.asp?image=http://209.164.24.44/exclusive/images/velious/velious6.jpg">Standing face to face with man’s best friend</a>
<li><a href="http://www.everlore.com/ShowScreenshot.asp?image=http://209.164.24.44/exclusive/images/velious/velious7.jpg">An orc camp in what I believe to be the IceClad Ocean</a>
</ul>
</p>
</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
		
				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="2">Xev server moves extended</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:catalyst@everlore.com">Catalyst</b></a>
				[11/30/2000-6:22:00 PM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=287946"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[1]</font></a>
				<p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><Blockquote>
<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/035309.html">XEV SERVER MOVE EXTENDED (For Povar and Tarew Marr)</a></B><P>

DEADLINE DATE FRIDAY DECEMBER 1st 11:59 P.M Pacific Standard Time.<P>

Good News for Povar and Tarew-Marr people who want to move ALL their characters from one server to the new server XEV. If you still want to move to the new server XEV please email <a href="mailto:eqmail@verant.com">eqmail@verant.com</a> and put in the subject heading:
XEV SERVER MOVE <P>

In the body of the message please include:
Your Name
Your STATION NAME(Its your EQ login name)
Your Account Key
and
Your last 6 digits of the original credit card.<P>

This is an all or nothing move. All characters from the original server will get moved.<P>

We will do our best to accommodate all people who request a move, but we can not guarantee we will move everybody. <P>

You must have your email submitted by FRIDAY DECEMBER 1st 11:59 P.M Pacific Standard Time.<P>

Good Luck<BR>
David Starr<BR>
Verant Interactive Technical and Customer Support
</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
		
				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="3">More news posts from Alan Vancouvering</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:catalyst@everlore.com">Catalyst</b></a>
				[11/30/2000-6:21:38 PM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=287761"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[3]</font></a>
				<p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><Blockquote>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/035739.html">Are the people who use the xp bug going to get banned?</a></B><P>

I found out today that there was a in bug game that allowed people to get from 56 to 60 (for ex.) in a couple hours. I would like to know if verant is going to ban this people like they should be.<P>

<B>If you know how this is being done and want to give me some details, please do.<P>

I know of a few of these bugs that are now fixed, and actually have been for a while.<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/035688.html">TV Guide</a></B><P>

<I>As most of you probably already know, EverQuest will be featured in TV Guide on December 9th.<P>

If you are interested in obtaining a copy but you don't subscribe to the magazine and you won't be able to get to a store to pick one up (say, for example, you don't live in the United States), there is a way that you can get a copy.<P>

Call 1-800-866-1400 or send an e-mail to <a href="mailto:tvg.customer.support@tvguide.com">tvg.customer.support@tvguide.com</a><P>

I've been told that it will cost $2.00 to purchase the issue this way (you will essentially be ordering a back order copy) and $3.00 to ship it internationally. But make sure to verify the cost with them when placing your order. They said that they will accept Visa, Mastercard, Discover, American Express, International Money Order or a check drawn on an American bank.<P>

EverQuest will be featured with some sort of article (I don't know what it's about) and the cover, with nice art (I don't know what the topic of the art will be either).<P>

Alan</I><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/035730.html">The lockdowns have commenced! Thanks for nothing, Verant!</a></B><P>

Threads regarding the nerf to pets are being locked, yet STILL there has been no response by Verant. AND NO, ABSOR'S THREAD REGARDING THE PROCCING WEAPON "FIX" DOES NOT COUNT! This is a separate issue! Thanks for once again ignoring your customers, VI!<P>

<B>Jax. Calm down. If you want to discuss this, please do so in the same threads with everyone else. Yelling at me and spamming the boards does not help you, it does not help me, and it harms others that want to discuss other issues.<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/035473.html">Patch #5 and WEF/HFL tailoring</a></B><P>

5 patches ago, Yakatizma told us about new and exciting Wood Elf and Halfling recepies that were added to Tailoring. AWESOME! Looks like some real nice stuff! The problem is, Yakatizma has not read the Boards since he posted that announcement, and two extremely critical components to those Racial Armors have been bugged.<P>

<B>I'll send this one to Yak (I hope he doesn't mind my abbreviating his name...). He's busy with all sorts of things at the moment, though...<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/034491.html">Paladin Epic Weapon Concerns</a></B><P>

There are currently two very outstanding but separate issues with the Paladins' Epic Weapon (Fiery Defender) which absolutely need some attention from Verant.
The first involves the model of the Fiery Defender. The second involves the effect on the Fiery Defender. Simply put, the current spell (Holy Shock, fire based 155 dd, 1.5 second stun) which the Fiery Defender processes is completely out of line with the effects on other Epic weapons. The effect should DEFINE the weapon, and does exactly that on the other weapons. On the Fiery Defender, the process is nothing more than a gimmick, and that’s not how it should be.<P>

<B>My answer, for you is: I don't know why this was done. I will look into it and see if I can get a reason why.<P>

Wow, that was the most incredibly short answer I could have given. Let me try to also address the original topics while I'm at it:<P>

I don't know why the proc was changed in the way it was and made resistable, I will look into that for you.<P>

I don't know if we can make it so that the blade shows and all other particle effects are reduced. I'll ask about that too.<P>

Sorry for taking so long to respond, I've been… busy. <P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/035732.html">Nec Pet unforseen proc change?</a></B><P>

At the 44th pet necro pets start proc'ing. You reduced the rate at which pets will proc. You reduced the amout of damage our pets will do (and get healed by) with this change. Question: Was this intended (nerf or bug)? 
Will the rate on this proc be increased (or damage done by it) so that our pets will be back to pre-patch status?<P>

<B>We only reduced the proc rate for pets using weapons.<P>

I'm going to have to lock this thread. Look for one of the longer threads for more information and discussion.<P>

Alan</B>
</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
		
