<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/035834.html">BUG!!! I can't see Spell effects!!!</a></B><P>

I have a 128 Rage GL PCI
and I can't see Spell effects...well some. I can see the blue (Healing spells) but I can't see A mage summon things (Green) and I can't see Buffs (also green) I cannot see fire blasts or snares. Just basically I can only see Healing spells.<P>

<B>Take a look at the level you've got set for your particle density. Change it to 'high'.<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/035804.html">Paladin Epic Weapon Concerns ( Fiery Defender Woes)</a></B><P>

Furthermore, the question here at the moment is the proc, and to a lesser extent the sword graphic (or lack thereof). Let's stay focused here else this is gonna turn into a huge whine thread in their eyes...<P>

<B>Well, I've learned one thing of interest to you.<P>

We do plan on making it so that you can choose particle density levels for World, Spells, and Weapons (items) separately. We'll look into this some time post Velious, but it's certainly something we plan to do.<P>

I don't have an answer for you about the proc…<P>

Alan</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/035783.html">Only 2 bags open at a time?</a></B><P>

So is there a reason we can only have 2 bags open at a time? It gets annoying trying to organize everything I have (loot, research stuff, food, water, etc...) with only 2 bags open at a time.<P>

<B>Yes, there is a reason. It's some sort of complicated coding reason…<P>

Unfortunately, as much as we also think it would be a great thing to be able to open more than two bags at a time, it won't happen any time soon, if ever.<P>

Alan</B><P>

