				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="17">EQ Fan Faire Event Press Release</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:catalyst@everlore.com">Catalyst</b></a>
				[11/29/2000-4:43:11 PM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=286686"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[0]</font></a>
				<p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><Blockquote>
Sony Online Entertainment's "EverQuest(r)" Official Fan Faire Event
Heads to 
the East Coast
<P>
EQ Fans to Meet and Greet the Creators and Their Fellow Norrathians in
Baltimore <P>
 
San Diego, CA - November 29, 2000 - Sony Online Entertainment is pleased
to announce 
that its next official "EverQuest(r)" Fan Faire Event location is to be
held 
in Baltimore, Maryland on February 2-3, 2001. At the event, EverQuest
fans will 
have the chance to meet the people that work behind the scenes to the
most successful 
online role- playing game in history and meet their fellow Norrathians.<P>

"The East Coast EverQuest fans have waited a long time," said Cindy
Archuleta, 
Community Relations Event Manager for Sony Online Entertainment. "We've
planned 
fun activities and panel discussions with different people from Sony
Online plus, 
this is the first event where contest prizes are actually in-game
items." <P>

The official launch party for "EverQuest(r): The Scars of Velious(tm)"
was a 
huge success that attracted over 1250 fans in Las Vegas November 4-5,
2000, making 
it one of the most well-attended events of its kind. Attendees were the
first 
to explore the new continent of Velious and mingle with the creators of
EverQuest. 
"I am looking forward to Baltimore," said Jeff Butler, producer of
"EverQuest: 
The Scars of Velious" and EQ Live. "It has been very valuable to meet
the players 
of EverQuest in past events, since the fans are the ones who have made
this game 
so successful." <P>

Where<BR>
BWI Airport Marriott<BR>
1743 West Nursery Road<BR>
Baltimore, MD<P>

Deadline<BR>
Registration deadline is January 22, 2001. The cost of attendance will
be $85 
and space is limited. Attendees must book their own travel and hotel
reservations. 
Sony Online has made arrangements with BWI Marriott for a special rate.<P>

For more information check out Sony's website at:
<BR><a href="http://www.station.sony.com/everquest/">http://www.station.sony.com/everquest/</a><P>

And BWI Airport Marriott's website:<BR>
<a href="http://www.marriotthotels.com/DPP/PropertyPage.asp?MarshaCode=BWIAP">http://www.marriotthotels.com/DPP/PropertyPage.asp?MarshaCode=BWIAP</a>
</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
		
